        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Frank</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I send a cheque for <hi rend="superscript">£</hi>50 which will clear all the bills mentioned by you.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> From what you say in your last note, I feel sure that you will be more careful for the future &amp; watch the money as it ouzes out. Altogether it is a rather heavy sum; but I know you &amp; trust you as a good dear affectionate son.—</p>
<p>Ever yours | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by a reference in CD’s Classed account books (Down House MS) dated 5 December 1870 to a payment to Francis of £50.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Francis was still at <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_795.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Cambridge University</ref>; see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to B. J. Sulivan, 20 December [1870]</ref> and n. 3.</note>
        </div>        
            
